3a:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-white/70 leading-relaxed mb-6","children":["Heating engineers suffer the most dramatic seasonal pattern. When temperatures drop below 5°C, boiler breakdown calls increase by ",["$","a",null,{"href":"/blog/i-lost-12000-in-one-winter-to-missed-boiler-calls-charlie-the-heating-engineer","className":"text-[var(--katie-blue)] hover:underline","children":"up to 340%"}],". The average emergency repair jumps from £180 to £280-450. And engineers are already at capacity — they can't answer phones while they're under floors or in lofts."]}]
3b:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-white/70 leading-relaxed mb-6","children":["January is catastrophic: 34% of all annual missed call losses happen in this single month. One Manchester heating engineer we tracked ",["$","a",null,{"href":"/blog/i-lost-12000-in-one-winter-to-missed-boiler-calls-charlie-the-heating-engineer","className":"text-[var(--katie-blue)] hover:underline","children":"missed 47 calls in one month"}],", losing an estimated £11,900 in revenue."]}]
